            .col-lg-6.mb-4
              h5.text-secondary.mb-3
                i.bi.bi-grid.me-2
                | Other Prioritization Methods
              p While not exclusively for hotfixes, these methods can be adapted:
              ul
                li.mb-2
                  strong Severity & Priority Ratings:
                  |  Assess impact on system and urgency of resolution
                li.mb-2
                  strong MoSCoW Method:
                  |  Hotfixes typically fall under "Must-have" category
                li.mb-2
                  strong RICE Scoring:
                  |  Evaluate Reach, Impact, Confidence, and Effort
                li.mb-2
                  strong Risk-Based Testing:
                  |  Prioritize based on potential risks and likelihood
                li.mb-2
                  strong Value vs. Effort Matrix:
                  |  Focus on high-value, low-effort fixes first
                li.mb-2
                  strong WSJF (Weighted Shortest Job First):
